{{italic title}} {{About|the painting|the baseball job|Manager (baseball)}} [[File:Roy Lichtenstein.jpg|thumb|upright|Lichtenstein in 1967]] '''''Baseball Manager''''' is a 1963 [[pop art]] painting by [[Roy Lichtenstein]]. The [[Magna (paint)|magna]] on canvas measures 68 x 56 inches. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lichtensteinfoundation.org/baseballman.htm |title=Baseball Manager |publisher=Roy Lichtenstein Foundation |accessdate=July 10, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130702054609/http://www.lichtensteinfoundation.org/baseballman.htm |archivedate=July 2, 2013 |df= }}</ref> The painting is visible at [[Marlins Park]] (Promenade Level, Section 19), located in Miami, Florida.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://miami.marlins.mlb.com/mia/ballpark/marlins_park_art.jsp|title=Marlins Park - The Visual Experience: Art in Public Places|accessdate=July 10, 2013|publisher=MLB Advanced Media}}</ref>
