The '''Santa Monica College of Design, Art and Architecture''' existed in [[Santa Monica, California]] from 1990 until 2000.  The director of the school was [[Joan Abrahamson]] who is a [[MacArthur Fellow]] and the founder and president of the [[Jefferson Institute]].  The school hosted an all professional faculty of working artists, designers and architects, among them [[Alison Saar]], [[Laddie John Dill]], George Herms, [[Jill Giegerich]], [[Lisa Adams (painter)|Lisa Adams]], Peter Alexander, Robert Wilhite and others.

